    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 528.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">London,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acquaint you that I
                            have just received from Mr. Harvey, the minister resident of the United
                            States at Lisbon, a telegram, the language of which is as follows:</p>
                <pb facs="0780" n="XXXII" xml:id="pg_XXXII"/>
                <p>“Please inform the department that cruiser Georgia has been depredating
                            near Teneriffe, and boarded Liverpool steamer Braganza last Sunday, one
                            hundred and fifty miles from here, heading northward towards British
                            channel. I have notified Kearsarge at Brest, and adopted all other
                            practical measures.”</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHARLES FRANCIS ADAMS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H, Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
